You can use macros (essentially functions) to check for children. e.g:


```{% macro menuItem(menuObj) %}
<li class="menu__item">
  <a href="{{ menuObj.link }}">{{ menuObj.label }}</a>
 {% if menuObj.children %}
   {{ renderMenu(menuObj.children) }}
 {% endif %}
</li>
{% endmacro %}

{% macro renderMenu(menuObj) %}
<ul class="menu__items">
  {% for item in menuObj.children %}
    {{ menuItem(item) }}
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endmacro %}

<nav>
<ul class="menu">
  {{ renderMenu(menu(module.menufield)) }}
</ul>
</nav>```

e.g.


```{% macro renderMenu(menuObj) %}
  {% set level = level + 1 %}
&lt;ul class="menu__items menu__items--level-{{ level }}"&gt;

  {% for item in menuObj.children %}
    {{ menuItem(item) }}
  {% endfor %}
&lt;/ul&gt;
{% endmacro %}```
